  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `erigon version 2021.10.4-alpha`\r\n\r\nOS & Version: `Linux 5.11.0-38-generic #42-Ubuntu SMP x86_64 GNU/Linux`\r\n\r\nCommit hash : `113a9be3b85b5996694a484f37b8a982ab38775b`\r\n\r\nErigon parameters: `erigon --nat any`\r\n\r\nRpcdaemon parameters: `rpcdaemon --datadir=/home/ptd/.local/share/erigon/ --http.addr=0.0.0.0 --http.api=eth,erigon,net,trace,debug --ws`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n`debug_accountRange` can be used to download the state of all accounts at a given block number.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n`debug_accountRange` leaks memory, eventually exhausting memory and crashing with `SIGBUS`.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n[This script](https://gist.github.com/ultratwo/81988c431360024b3686cf9d7e5a236d) attempts to download every single account as it was at block 10. Running it causes a rapid memory leak.\r\n\r\nThe extent of the memory leak seems to be related to the how far into the account range the request goes. Repeatedly requesting the first account (by replacing the `next_token = reply[\"result\"][\"next\"]` with `pass`) immediately leaks 2GB, but doesn't leak any more memory regardless of how many times the request is repeated.\r\n",
